Exercise -> Screenshot(314) - ?? -> https://academy.ehacking.net/courses/550930/lectures/9988044

- DaRT(Diagnostics and Recovery Toolset) tool kit can be used to delete the SAM file in Windows

- Password and Registry Editor - ?? -> https://academy.ehacking.net/courses/550930/lectures/9988055

- 'chntpw' is a software utility for reseting or blanking local passwords used by Windows, it does this by editing the SAM database
where windows stores password hashes.

Ques -> You've gained physical access to a Windows 2008 R2 server which has an accessible disc drive. When you attempt to boot the 
server and log in, you are unable to guess the password. In your tool kit you have an Ubuntu 9.10 Linux Live CD. Which Linux based
tool has the ability to change any user's password or to activate disabled Windows accounts?
Ans -> chntpw
))

